<h1>Paul Miller</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://justplainpaul.com/now/">justplainpaul.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Indianapolis
IN
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Current Musical Projects: justplainpaul, guitarist for Rivetshack and guitarist for Reluctor.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I create, and I help the world understand the behavior of sound.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I create because it is vital to my well being. I love expressing ideas and bringing them to life.  It is also my way of leading by example, so that my child can see anything is possible with the right attitude and mindset.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
It is never too late to break loose.  Obligations and duties are not shackles, they are part of the servitude and process to give back to society.  The only element that hinders your freedom is your willingness to pursue it.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"Never Eat Alone and Other Secrets to Success, One Relationship at a Time" by Keith Ferrazzi with Tahl Raz
</p>

